      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is Google My Business called now?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Google My Business was renamed to Google Business Profile (GBP) in 2022. The features, dashboard, and functionality remain identical — only the name changed. Many businesses still use "GMB" interchangeably.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the best Google My Business tool for a single-location business?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">For single-location businesses, theStacc Local SEO ($49/mo) handles automated content creation, BrightLocal ($39/mo) provides tracking and auditing, and Google Business Profile (free) serves as the foundation. Combined cost: $88/month for a complete content + tracking stack.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How often should I post to my Google Business Profile?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">3–5 times weekly is optimal. Businesses posting daily or near-daily consistently rank higher in local pack results. The minimum to see any benefit is once weekly. theStacc creates 30 posts monthly, fully automated — no manual work required.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do GBP posts actually help with local rankings?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Google confirms profile activity as a local ranking factor. GBP posts signal business engagement and provide keyword-rich content that Google indexes. Regular posting shows measurable visibility improvements within 4–8 weeks.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I manage Google My Business without paid tools?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. GBP is free with full features. Everything requires manual effort. If you can dedicate 3–5 hours per week to manual posting and management, paid tools aren't strictly necessary. Most business owners can't sustain that cadence, which is where tools earn their keep.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How do I track my Google Maps ranking?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">BrightLocal and Local Falcon both offer geo-grid rank tracking — geographic grid scanning that produces visual heatmaps showing your Maps position at the neighborhood level. Costs range $24.99–$59/month. BrightLocal also includes audit and citation tracking in the same subscription.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
